// =============================================================================
// Arukellt Standard Prelude — auto-imported into every Arukellt module
// =============================================================================
//
// Compilation: RFC-005 / #816 restores prelude decls to the backend combine
// path. CoreOp-bound symbols and intrinsic shims defer MIR body lowering until
// #821/#822 (see mir/lower/stdlib_body_defer.ark). Pure Ark helpers such as
// contains_i32 are lowered now.
//
// ## Tiny Prelude (canonical v3+ surface — ≤ 15 symbols)
//
// The intended minimal prelude for Arukellt programs going forward:
//
//   Types / compiler builtins (handled by ark-typecheck, not listed here):
//     Option, Result, String, Bytes, Vec
//     Some, None, Ok, Err
//
//   Functions provided by THIS file (the canonical tiny set):
//     panic, assert
//     String_from, String_new
//     char_to_string  (essential conversion)
//     plus len, push, pop, get, set, get_unchecked (compiler intrinsics)
//
// ## Legacy / Compat Section (deprecated — bold cutover per ADR-036)
//
// **Monomorphic Vec constructors** (`Vec_new_i32`, `Vec_new_i64`, …) and all
// monomorphic higher-order functions (`map_i32_i32`, `filter_i32`, …) are
// **deprecated** and will be removed via **bold cutover** (ADR-036 D2) once
// issues #688–#697 (trait-based stdlib redesign) are complete.
//
use std::collections::string
use std::core::scalar_format

// The correct migration target is **trait-based method syntax**, not the
// intermediate `std::text` / `std::seq` explicit-import style:
//
//   | Deprecated (this file)        | Trait-based replacement (post-#688) |
//   |-------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
//   | `Vec_new_i32()`               | `Vec::new()` (generic, #697)         |
//   | `map_i32_i32(v, f)`           | `v.map(f)` (Iterator trait, #691)    |
//   | `filter_i32(v, f)`            | `v.filter(f)` (Iterator trait, #691) |
//   | `sort_i32(v)`                 | `v.sort()` (Vec method, #697)        |
//   | `concat(a, b)`                | `a.concat(b)` (String method)        |
//   | `(n).to_string()`            | `n.to_string()` (Display trait, #702)|
//   | `clone(s)`                    | `s.clone()` (Clone trait, #692)       |
//   | `eq(a, b)`                    | `a.eq(b)` (Eq trait, #695)            |
//
// Per ADR-036 D5, free functions like `clone`, `eq`, `i32_to_string` will
// remain as thin wrappers delegating to their trait impls, so existing
// call sites continue to work during the transition.
//
// Design ADR:    docs/adr/ADR-036-trait-stdlib-redesign.md
// Prelude design: docs/stdlib/prelude.md
//
// =============================================================================
// String construction
pub fn String_from(s: String) -> String {
    return s
}

pub fn String_new() -> String {
    panic(String_new()); return String_new()
}

// String comparison
pub fn eq(a: String, b: String) -> bool {
    string::eq(a, b)
}

